  "setupEncryption": "Set Up Encryption",
  "faqQuestion1": "What is end-to-end encryption?",
  "faqAnswer1": "End-to-end encryption means your messages are encrypted before sending and only decrypted when they reach the recipient. Throughout the entire transmission process, including servers and any intermediate nodes, no one can view the original message content. Only the sender and recipient can read the messages.",
  "faqQuestion2": "What happens if I lose my key?",
  "faqAnswer2": "If you lose your encryption key, you will not be able to decrypt any future encrypted messages. Make sure to back up your key securely.",
  "faqQuestion3": "Can I change my key?",
  "faqAnswer3": "Yes, you can generate a new key or import a different one at any time. Messages are decrypted when received, so changing your key will not affect previously received messages.",
  "faqQuestion4": "Is my key stored on the server?",
  "faqAnswer4": "No. Your encryption key is stored only on your device using secure storage. The server never has access to your key.",
  "faqQuestion5": "What encryption algorithm is used?",
  "faqAnswer5": "We use AES-256-GCM (Advanced Encryption Standard with 256-bit keys in Galois/Counter Mode). This is a widely validated symmetric encryption algorithm that provides strong security and data integrity protection.",
  "importKeyDescription": "Paste your 32-byte AES key (Base64)",
  "importKeyHint": "Enter Base64 encoded key...",

